channel.title: Need Help with JDK/My Complier?
channel.description:
When I try to Compile it says..:
You do not have JDK 5.0 or JDK 6.0 or any JDK 5.0 or JDK 6.0 updates.
Yet I downloaded JDK 6 Update 6, Un-installed, Re-installed, still says that MSG, is it the Compiler? If Not.. Can anyone give me some tips on how to fix this?
PLEASE HELP! -- Thanks; Aftermath

item.title: Need Help with JDK/My Complier?
item.dc:creator: @Username Username
item.description:
@Username wrote:

Replace your compiler with this.

:: ::
:: This Compiler is under no licenses and may ::
:: be distributed freely. ::
:: ::
::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

@echo off
if exist “%programfiles%\Java” (call :compile “%programfiles%\Java”) else (goto error)
:compile
for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe")
if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java)
if defined p (goto end)
:error
echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load.
“%programfiles%\Internet Explorer\iexplore.exe” http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp
:end
echo Finished!
pause
exit[/code]
